article.headline: TCU 70, Tulane 65
article.story: FORT WORTH, Texas (AP) -- Corey Santee scored 16 points and hit two free throws with less than a minute to play to lead TCU to a 70-65 win over Tulane on Saturday night. Santee's foul shots came with 50 seconds to play broke a 65-65 tie, then Nucleus Smith added a layup and free throw for TCU (5-8, 1-1 Conference USA). Marcus Shropshire added 15 points for the Horned Frogs and Chudi Chinweze scored 10 points and grabbed eight rebounds. Wayne Tinsley scored 18 points to lead Tulane (6-6, 0-2). Vytas Tatarunas scored 14 points and pulled down 10 rebounds. Vincent Camper added 10 points for the Green Wave. Tulane led 33-29 at halftime.
